{
  "stem": "9446.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Neither is Rotwand.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But anyway, it was a very prominent school in Warsaw, in Poland-- an excellent school.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "In addition to being an electrical engineer, my father also went to Berlitz School of Languages.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And he mastered English beautifully.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He probably spoke English much better than most Americans do here.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And he also knew French, and Russian, and Polish, of course.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Now I must say something about Russia.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I mentioned before to you that Poland was-- I don't know if you are aware of it, but Poland is in a very unfortunate geographical position being between Germany and Russia.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And it was very often invaded by both of those countries.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And as a result of the invasion, it was divided into German part of Poland occupied by the Germans and the Russian-- the Russians-- for the times of Czar.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "That was the times of the Czar, you know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And the southern part of Poland was occupied by the Austrians.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "That left a definite mark on the history of Poland, of course.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And one of the reasons why my father was so fluent in Russian is because Warsaw, Warsaw, where we come from, and where he came from, was occupied by the Russians.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "So Russian was the dominate-- the dominating language, you know.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And that was the-- that's the history of Poland is one almost continuous tragedy.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "So it definitely creates a life difficult for everybody in Poland.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Now let me just make one comment on Jewish life in Poland.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Now Poles, most of the Polish people, were anti-Semitism And that's an old story.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Now what was responsible primarily for the anti-Semitism in Poland was the clergy, the church.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
